---
import Layout from '../../components/Layout.astro';
import LatentLens from '../../components/v22/LatentLens.astro';
import { repositoryCommits } from '../../data/observatory';
---
<Layout title="LLM Steering — Systems Observatory" description="An activation-steering workbench where model behavior becomes an inspectable, validated experiment." canonicalPath="/systems/llm-steering/">
  <section class="flagship-hero steering-flagship"><div class="shell"><span>OPEN-SOURCE FLAGSHIP / REPRESENTATION ENGINEERING</span><h1>Model behavior becomes an inspectable experiment.</h1><p>Compare a baseline, prompt-only control, and activation-steered output across layer, coefficient, token scope, and hook stage—without confusing a visible delta with universal reliability.</p><div><a class="signal-button" href="https://github.com/smgpulse007/llm-steering">Repository ↗</a><small>PINNED SOURCE / {repositoryCommits.llmSteering.slice(0,12)}</small></div></div></section>
  <section class="v22-scene lens-scene"><div class="shell scene-heading"><div><span>01 / LATENT LENS</span><h2>Read the result beside the intervention.</h2></div><p>Every sentence shown here comes from the pinned checked-in showcase artifact. No live generation occurs in the browser.</p></div><div class="shell"><LatentLens/></div></section>
  <section class="v22-scene harness-contracts"><div class="shell scene-heading"><div><span>02 / EXPERIMENT CONTRACT</span><h2>Controls before conclusions.</h2></div><p>Model support, artifact validation, and observed deltas are separate claims.</p></div><div class="shell contract-orbit">{['Baseline','Prompt-only control','Vector extraction','Layer + coefficient','Pre/post hook','Validated artifact'].map((name,i)=><article><span>{String(i+1).padStart(2,'0')}</span><strong>{name}</strong><p>{['Unmodified model response','Language-only comparison','Direction from prompt pairs','Explicit intervention coordinates','Activation location and timing','Schema, metadata, and result'][i]}</p></article>)}</div></section>
  <section class="v22-scene limitation-field"><div class="shell"><div><span>SUPPORT BOUNDARY</span><h2>Compatibility is a registry, not a guess.</h2></div><ul><li>Gemma 4 E2B is the verified steering-ready target in the pinned registry.</li><li>Other Gemma, Phi, Ministral, DiffusionGemma, and Qwen paths require validation or remain experimental.</li><li>A visible output delta is not a guarantee of quality, safety, or generalization.</li></ul></div></section>
</Layout>
